      "writtenOn": "2021-05-17T21:05:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmmm... I like the idea but was going to push back on resource IDs (because they require a resource manager to resolve) and propose using a general InputStream instead.\n\nOn second thought, a resource manager is exactly what we\u0027re going to need to support external resources (images etc).\n\nI think this will fit nicely with a builder pattern similar to the native side:\n\n  SkottieAnimation.Builder()\n      .setResources(getResources())\n      .setLogger(...)\n      .makeFromResource(ID); // or makeFromStream(), or makeFromString()\n\nLet\u0027s leave as is for now and I\u0027ll circle back with a builder?",
      "parentUuid": "25f0dce7_1bb052be",
      "revId": "6c97c39895067e3252daf1762714a86aff85e369",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
